observations.recommendation:
Ensure issuance of Acknowledgment Receipts to all future receipts of donations in-kind to confirm that donations are properly recorded and accounted for; 

Ensure that all future issuances of donated items are properly supported with Issuance Form for In-Kind Donations or any document/record to prove receipt by and distribution to the intended beneficiaries; and

Determine the inventory of remaining undistributed items, if any, for recording in the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM.

MEE Administrator to-

update its financial records and compute the correct amount of the uncollected balances from the contract of lease as of December 31, 2019;

furnish the Municipal Accountant’s Office, copies of the previous and current notarized contract of lease of stallholders;

coordinate with Municipal Treasurer’s Office and Municipal Accountant's Office for the proper record keeping and prompt collection of the said uncollected balances. 

Municipal Accountant to-

prepare appropriate adjusting entries to record the uncollected balances from stallholders as of December 31, 2019; and

ensure that the succeeding revenues from contract lease will be recorded in accordance with accrual basis and Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards;

Issue policies and guidelines in hiring JO and Contract of Service of Personnel in Legislative and Executive Offices;

Ensure that the hiring of JO personnel be put into an agreement by entering into Job Order and incorporated therein the services to be rendered and the number of man-hours, quantity, and duration of the work to be performed;

Strengthen the controls in the hiring of job order by requiring them to submit personal records, undergo an interview, and document the evaluation of performance to give assurance that the risk identified above are address; and

Require all JOs to submit a properly prepared accomplishment report based on their actual duties and activities performed and to use computer-generated DTRs based on the captured biometric data, except for those in the field, for the establishment of a reliable number of days worked as the basis for the computation of their wages.

Require the appropriate Office of the Municipality to stop the practice of procuring airline tickets from travel agencies and enroll / enter into MOA with PS DBM Government Fare Agreement. Moving forward, to procure airline tickets within the GFA in order to avail discounts and other privileges/benefits; 

While registration with GFA is in process, require that the procurement of airline tickets will be made directly from the airlines companies to avoid similar excessive charges and fees;

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit the original official receipts issued by the ticketing agencies for all travels as per attached schedule within 15 days from receipt hereof.

We recommended Management to direct the Municipal Treasurer and Accountant to: 
Discontinue the payment of cash gift earlier than the prescribed period;
Update themselves on the existing guidelines on the payment of cash gift and other emoluments for Elected Officials and Employees, particularly DBM Circular No. 2016-4 and Local Budget Circular No. 121, to ensure proper release of the said benefits.

