Instruct the Office of the Municipal Engineer to exert extra effort to complete the preparation of the program of works of new or re-aligned projects;

Instruct the Office of the Municipal Planning and Development Office to settle the problems on road right-of-way, and the finalization of the sanitary landfill plan;

Follow-up the Provincial Government for the implementation of the 2nd Diversion Road; and 

Instruct the Local Development Council to judiciously plan the inclusion of priority projects to be included in the 20% Development Fund to avoid re-alignment to new projects which resulted to the non-implementation of funded projects.

The end-user offices to meticulously and judiciously prepare the Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) in accordance with Section 7.3.2 of the RIRR of the RA No. 9184 to avoid delay in the implementation of programs and projects;

The BAC Secretariat and the BAC Chairperson to meticulously check the PPMPs prepared by the end-user units before consolidating it to the APP to facilitate the efficient conduct of procurement activities for every procurement project; and

The Municipal Accountant ensure that PPMPs prepared by the end-user units were in accordance to the RIRR of the RA No. 9184 before certifying the correctness of the said Plan.

The Municipal Treasurer to strictly monitor the collections and remittances of the revenue collectors and instruct the revenue collectors to remit their collections daily and intact;

The Municipal Treasurer ensure that collections made from the previous accountable forms are remitted and/or deposited before granting the requisition of additional accountable form to prevent accumulation of unremitted collections;

The Revenue Collectors to report and record promptly their collections and remittances on their cashbook; and

The management to install internal policy for the strict monitoring of the collections and remittances/deposits on the Office of the Municipal Treasurer to prevent misappropriation and/or misuse of government funds; and consider the hiring or designation of a Liquidating Officer to assist the Municipal Treasurer in the monitoring of collections and remittances of the Revenue Collectors.

The Management submit the MOA/Trust Agreement between the barangay government and the Municipality to determine the validity, legality and propriety of the fund transfer to its barangays;

Require the barangay government to submit Program of Works of its development projects funded by the Municipality, and the liquidation reports of the fund received to validate the implementation of the projects being funded; and

Municipal Accountant ensure that fund transfers to barangays are properly supported with complete documentation.

The Municipal Engineering Office and other offices to prepare Program of Works and/or Work and Financial Plan to support the requisition and procurement of gasoline, oil and lubricants;

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to procure the petroleum products in accordance with the Implementing Rules and Regulations of the Republic Act No. 9184; and 

The Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant ensure the completeness of supporting documents before approving disbursement for petroleum products.

The Requisitioning Office to indicate the essential information on the preparation of Purchase Request;

The Municipal Treasurer ensure that Purchase Request is completely filled-up; and

The Municipal Accountant ensure that all supporting documents are complete, properly filled-up with all the essential data and duly acknowledged by the supplier before processing the disbursement of government funds.
